        <tags>cvss_base_vector=AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:N/I:N/A:C|summary=Adminer is prone to a denial of service (DoS) vulnerability.|insight=When using Monolog for logging, Adminer allows a denial of
  service (memory consumption) via a crafted serialized payload (e.g., using s:1000000000),
  leading to a PHP Object Injection issue.|affected=Adminer version 4.8.1 and prior.|impact=Remote, unauthenticated attackers can trigger this by sending a
  malicious serialized object, which forces excessive memory usage, rendering Adminer's interface
  unresponsive and causing a server-level DoS. While the server may recover after several minutes,
  multiple simultaneous requests can cause a complete crash requiring manual intervention.|solution=Update to version 4.8.2 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 4.8.2 or later.</solution>
